'''
Harshad Number:If a number is divisible by the sum of its digits, then it will be known as a Harshad Number.
For example:The number 156 is divisible by the sum (12) of its digits(1,5,6).
Some Harshad numbers are 8, 54, 120, etc.
'''
n=int(input("Enter a number:"))
num=n
s=0
while n>0:
    r=n%10
    s=s+r
    n=n//10
if num%s==0:
    print(num,"is a Harshad Number")
else:
    print(num,"is not a Harshad Number")
